            <div id="equity" class="tab-content active">
                <h3 style="margin-bottom: 20px; color: #667eea;">üìä US Equities & Sector Breakdown (July 2025 Update)</h3>

                <div class="card" style="margin-bottom: 20px; background: rgba(234, 179, 8, 0.08);">
                    <h4 style="color: #eab308; margin-bottom: 15px;">‚ö†Ô∏è Current Flow Environment: Weakening</h4>
                    <p style="color: #d0d0e8; line-height: 1.6;">
                        July 2025 TIC inflows collapsed to <strong>$2.1B</strong> (from $398B peak Sep '24). Foreign official outflows of -$20.5B signal reduced central bank demand.
                        NFCI extremely loose (-0.53) providing technical support, but flow deterioration warrants <strong>defensive positioning with reduced size</strong>.
                    </p>
                </div>

